article.linkText: McCray's 16 lead Jacksonville past North Florida 62-50
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- — Robert McCray scored 16 points as Jacksonville beat North Florida 62-50 on Friday night. McCray added eight rebounds for the Dolphins (14-14, 5-9 Atlantic Sun Conference). Bryce Workman added 13 points while shooting 5 of 9 from the field and 3 for 8 from the line, and he also had 10 rebounds and three steals. Marcus Niblack shot 4 of 11 from the field and 2 for 3 from the line to finish with 12 points. The Ospreys (15-14, 8-6) were led by Jah Nze, who recorded 17 points. Chaz Lanier added 13 points for North Florida. Jasai Miles also had eight points. Both teams play again on Wednesday. Jacksonville hosts Stetson and North Florida hosts FGCU. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
